w types of content and edit already existing content types. By default, Drupal includes the content types Article and Basic Page. Articles are typically used for more blog-like content, whereas Basic Pages are usually used for static content.\r\n\r\n<b>Editing An Already Existing Content Type</b>\r\nTo edit an already existing content type, click edit, manage fields, or manage display. Once you click on edit, manage fields, or manage display, the other links will show up as tabs when you’re editing the content type. Here, we’re on the edit tab and can see Manage Fields, Manage Display, Comment Fields, and Comment Display as other options.\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.csteachingtips.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/4.png\"><img src=\"http://blog.csteachingtips.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/4.png\" alt=\"4\" width=\"314\" height=\"196\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.csteachingtips.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/8.png\"><img src=\"http://blog.csteachingtips.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/8.png\" alt=\"8\" width=\"780\" height=\"455\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-39\" /></a>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n','Learning the Drupal GUI','','inherit','open','open','','16-revision-v1','','','2014-08-13 23:28:26','2014-08-13 23:28:26','',16,'http://blog.csteachingtips.org/?p=40',0,'revision','',0),(42,1,'2014-08-13 23:30:04','2014-08-13 23:30:04','','9','','inherit','open','open','','9','','','2014-08-13 23:30:04','2014-08-13 23:30:04','',16,'http://blog.csteachingtips.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/9.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(43,1,'2014-08-13 23:30:25','2014-08-13 23:30:25','Once our team decided that Drupal was our CMS (Content Management System) of choice, our first challenge was learning how to use the Drupal GUI (Graphical User Interface). This may seem like it would be an extremely simple task. That appearance of simplicity is somewhat deceiving.\r\n\r\nWhile there is Drupal documentation available both on <a href = 